101.dialogue: The race has started. I can't wait to see who'll win.

102.dialogue: Allow me to play you a victory song.

103.dialogue: You'll choose me? Aww, thanks. You're my dear racerâ™¡

104.dialogue: Listen to this intense song and focus.

105.dialogue: Going slow is fine, too. It's safer.

107.dialogue: Keep it up! The finish line is in sight!

108.dialogue: That's the spirit! Just like that!

109.dialogue: Heehee. I knew you'd pull through.

111.dialogue: Not bad at all. I thought you'd lose your cool!

112.dialogue: What? The record? You did break the top speed record.

113.dialogue: Heheh. Can't get enough of my support, can ya?

114.dialogue: It might not look like it, but I AM rootin' for ya. Don't get your ass kicked.

115.dialogue: Took you a while. Had any technical problems? C'mon, victory's just 'round the corner.

116.dialogue: I'm rooting for ya. Just gotta believe in yourself.

117.dialogue: Reckon you can set a new record?

118.dialogue: I'm cheerin' for ya. Ain't no way you're gonna lose.

119.dialogue: Heh! I can already taste the gold trophy.

121.dialogue: You're ready for the race. Let's stay in peak condition.

122.dialogue: Let us thank the Holy Iris for its blessings. Granted, this was more thanks to your talent, Commander.

123.dialogue: Together, let us seize victory once more.

124.dialogue: I'm praying for you. Continue onward.

125.dialogue: Do you think you should service your car one more time?

126.dialogue: Safety first. Let's keep moving forward diligently.

127.dialogue: I will judge you based on your placing. Okay, that was a joke. Slow and steady wins the race.

128.dialogue: You're getting better. Have the blessings given you new talent?

129.dialogue: I saw it. Victory awaits your arrival.
